standardCDF(double, boolean) - Static method in class dr.math.distributions.NormalDistribution
A more accurate and faster implementation of the cdf (taken from function pnorm in the R statistical language) This implementation has discrepancies depending on the programming language and system architecture In Java, returned values become zero once z reaches -37.5193 exactly on the machine tested In the other implementation, the returned value 0 at about z = -8 In C, this 0 value is reached approximately z = -37.51938

Will later need to be optimised for BEAST
